3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bybit calculates SOL/USDT funding rates using a time-weighted average of the premium index over the 8-hour period, with rates applied at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC. The premium index tracks the difference between the perpetual price and the underlying SOL spot index across multiple exchanges. When funding is positive, long positions pay shorts; when negative, shorts pay longs. Bybit's unified trading account allows seamless hedging across spot and derivatives without separate wallet transfers."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","SOL","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SOL/USDT represents the second-largest altcoin perpetual market by volume, often experiencing dramatic funding rate swings during Solana ecosystem events or broader market volatility. The pair's deep liquidity and tight spreads on Bybit enable efficient entry and exit for arbitrage positions. Solana's correlation with broader DeFi trends creates predictable funding patterns that experienced arbitrageurs can exploit."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SOL/USDT funding rates on Bybit have ranged from -0.375% to +0.375% during extreme market conditions, with typical rates oscillating between -0.01% and +0.05%. During Solana network upgrades or major DeFi protocol launches, funding often skews positive as retail traders increase long exposure. Bear market periods frequently see sustained negative funding as institutional players maintain short hedges. The 8-hour intervals provide sufficient time for sophisticated arbitrageurs to capture rate differentials across exchanges."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Cross-Exchange Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bybit's SOL/USDT funding rates often diverge from Binance and OKX by 0.01-0.03%, creating profitable arbitrage windows. The exchange's fast matching engine and competitive 0.02% maker fees enable efficient hedging strategies across venues. Bybit's unified account structure eliminates internal transfer delays, crucial for time-sensitive funding rate plays. During high volatility periods, funding differentials can exceed 0.05%, offering substantial profit potential for well-capitalized arbitrageurs with multi-exchange setups."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SOL's price volatility can quickly erode funding rate profits if hedging positions aren't properly maintained across exchanges. Bybit's mark price methodology uses multiple spot exchanges, but sudden liquidity events can cause temporary tracking errors. The unified trading account requires careful monitoring of cross-margin ratios when running large arbitrage positions. Solana network congestion has historically caused spot-perpetual basis disruptions that can impact funding calculations and create unexpected P&L swings for arbitrage strategies."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"What are typical SOL/USDT funding rates on Bybit?","answer":"SOL/USDT funding rates on Bybit typically range from -0.01% to +0.05% per 8-hour period under normal market conditions. During extreme bullish sentiment or Solana ecosystem events, rates can spike above 0.1%, while bear markets often see sustained negative rates around -0.02%."},{"question":"How does Bybit's unified account affect SOL funding arbitrage?","answer":"Bybit's unified trading account allows instant hedging between SOL spot and perpetual positions without wallet transfers, reducing execution delays crucial for funding rate arbitrage. This eliminates the settlement risk and timing inefficiencies present on exchanges requiring separate derivative and spot wallets."},{"question":"When do SOL funding rates reset on Bybit?","answer":"Bybit applies SOL/USDT funding rates at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC daily. The rate calculation begins approximately 15 minutes before each settlement time, using the time-weighted average premium index over the preceding 8-hour period."},{"question":"What's the minimum position size for SOL funding arbitrage on Bybit?","answer":"Bybit's SOL/USDT perpetual has a minimum order size of 0.1 SOL, but effective funding rate arbitrage typically requires positions of at least 100-500 SOL to overcome trading fees and achieve meaningful profit margins. The unified account enables precise hedging ratios without minimum balance constraints across trading pairs."}]}]
